o bring the most recognized lawn and garden brands in the industry our headquarters is located in marysville ohio where om scott began selling lawn seed in  the company has grown to be an industry leader with regional offices and research facilities across the us and businesses in canada europe and asia pacific   industry leader scottsmiraclegro has helped to grow the more than  billion global consumer lawn and garden market by staying connected with the consumer through our consumer insights and dedication to innovation we continue to bring trusted lawn and garden products to consumers worldwide   our brands in the us scotts® miraclegro® ortho® and tomcat® brands are market leading in their categories as is the consumer roundup® brand which is marketed in north america and most of europe exclusively by scotts outside of north america the company has various popular brands including miraclegro® evergreen® kb® fertiligene® celaflor® and substral® our brands are sold through the world’s leading home improvement retailers and mass merchandisers other key channels include large hardware chain stores independent hardware stores garden centers nurseries greenhouses and food and drug stores view all brands resources download logos and assets sign up for media alerts newsroom is there anything grit can’t do  june   california’s drought emergency is over but water conservation must continue gov brown declares  april   talent counts but effort counts twice  march   greater access to clean water greenspaces and education building a stronger foundation for healthy communities  february   solving algal blooms requires many disciplines  february   press releases scottsmiraclegro announces timing of third quarter  results and conference call  tue  jul   gmt new survey shows protecting honeybees and other pollinators is a major concern among americans  mon  jun   gmt scottsmiraclegro updates fiscal  sales and adjusted eps outlook  tue  jun   gmt scottsmiraclegro to present at william blair  company’s th annual growth stock conference  tue  may   gmt scotts miraclegro company  wikipedia scotts miraclegro company from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from the scotts miraclegro company jump to navigation search the scotts miraclegro company type public traded as nyse smg sp  component industry manufacturing founded   years ago  headquarters marysville ohio us key people om scott founder james hagedorn ceo and chairman of the board michael c lukemire coo and president products products for lawn and garden care revenue  billion usd  net income  million usd  number of employees  website scottsmiraclegrocom the scotts miraclegro company is an american multinational corporation headquartered in marysville ohio where om scott began selling lawn seed in  the company is considered an industry leader in the lawn and garden market with regional offices and research facilities across the us and businesses in canada europe and asia pacific in the us the companys scotts miraclegro and ortho brands are market leading in their categories as is the consumer roundup brand which is marketed in north america and most of europe exclusively by scotts outside of north america the companys brands include miraclegro evergreen kb fertiligene celaflor and substral contents  overview  history  sale of bird seed in –  gm grass  peat bogs in the uk  mergers and acquisitions  brands  united states  outside the us  references  external links overviewedit the scotts miraclegro company manufactures provides doityourself lawn garden and home protection products in north america europe and asia pacific among their offerings are consumer fertilizers plant foods soils and mulches pest controls grass seed and bird food the companys principal consumer brands in north america are scotts miraclegro and ortho in addition scotts is monsantos exclusive agent for the marketing and distribution of consumer roundup scotts lawnservice serves the doitforme consumer in the us with onsite lawn tree and shrub fertilization insect control and other related services through its network of  locations scotts lawnservice is considered a leader of this usd billion categorycitation needed in  the company reported net sales of  billion a  increase in the second half of the year and an adjusted income of  millioncitation needed historyedit this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed september  learn how and when to remove this template message scotts headquarters in marysville scotts was founded in  by orlando scott as a premium seed company for the us agricultural industry in the early s the company began a lawn grass seed business for homeowners and in  became the first to ship grass seed products directly to stores prior to that consumers could purchase scotts seed only through the mail by  scottss sales had reached  and the company had  associates for the next  years the company focused on developing new products to combat weeds fertilize grass and develop automated electronic seed processing and packaging plants in the early s scotts started selling a program of products for lawns established special training classes to help retailers better assist customers in developing their lawns received a us patent for trionized bonding which produced fertilizers that delivered sustained feeding and introduced a complete line of turf builder combination products by the end of  the company had added two new divisions to its portfolio the golf course division developed to promote an exclusive line of professional products for golf courses and other large institutional accounts and scotts lawnservice established after scotts found a significant doitforme customer segmentation the service offers onsite lawn tree and shrub fertilization insect control and other related services through its network of  locations the company also launched a directtoconsumer helpline allowing lawn owners to call scotts for advice and assistance later that year privately owned om scott  sons was purchased by itt the international business conglomerate fifteen years later scotts became an independent company through a leveraged buyout from itt in  scotts became a publicly traded company with an initial offering of  a share three years later it merged with miraclegro a gardening company to create the scotts miraclegro company during the united states presidential election  the company endorsed the election of republican party candidate mitt romney sale of bird seed in –edit on january   scotts miraclegro agreed to plead guilty in federal court and pay  million in fines for selling  million units of bird seed from november  to march  that was coated with pesticide known to be deadly to birds and fish pesticides were added to protect the product from insects during storage notwithstanding that storcide ii one of the pesticides used was clearly marked as extremely toxic to birds records show that its own experts warned of the risk in the summer and fall of  and yet scotts continued to sell the deadly product until march  in  scotts miraclegro also falsified pesticide registration numbers required by the us environmental protection agency on its products on september   in ohio a federal court sentenced scotts to pay a  million fine and perform community service for  criminal violations of the federal insecticide fungicide and rodenticide act fifra in a separate agreement with the environmental protection agency scotts agreed to pay more than  million in penalties and spend  million on environmental projects according to the justice department both the criminal and civil settlements are the largest under fifra to date gm grassedit scotts has developed several genetically modified grasses including herbicidetolerant kentucky bluegrass and creeping bentgrass in  the us department of agriculture fined scotts miraclegro  when modified dna from gm creeping bentgrass was found within relatives of the same genus agrostis as well as in native grasses up to  km  mi from the test sites peat bogs in the ukedit in  scotts was involved in a major dispute with nature conservation bodies and the uk government about the future of several peat bogs in the north of england under pressure from the european union the uk government moved to declare a number of peat bogs covering an area of  acres in yorkshire and cumbria as special areas of conservation thus ending scotts ability to harvest peat for their garden products during the course of the dispute nick kirkbride the then managing director of scotts in britain described the peat bogs as having no more conservation interest than a ploughed field the peat bogs were eventually saved from further destruction by the payment by the uk government of compensation of £ million to scotts for loss of the right to extract peat mergers and acquisitionsedit   the om scott  sons company was incorporated   scotts introduced its retail product line into canada through a distributorship arrangement with home hardware   scotts acquired the lawn and garden business of hyponex corporation the largest producer and marketer of organic growing media products in the us   scotts acquired republic tool  manufacturing company providing total quality control over the manufacture of scotts spreaders   scotts acquired the gracesierra horticultural products company adding controlledrelease fertilizer technologies such as osmocote along with other brands including metromix banrot and peters in addition sierra also brought on board a wellestablished international organization for manufacturing sales and distribution this organization began in  when archer daniels midland company produced the firstever resincoated controlledrelease fertilizer   scotts merged with miraclegro products inc   miracle care garden ltd approximately a third of the growing uk lawn and garden products company was owned by miraclegro at the time of the  merger and in january  scotts purchased the remaining interest in the company   scotts acquired emerald green lawn service which would become scotts lawn service in    scotts purchased privately held levington horticulture ltd to expand into the uk horticulture market   the company acquired the organics company earthgro inc expanding access to mass merchant retailers and home centers in the northeast region   the company acquired  ownership of plant breeding company sanford scientific inc ssi   scotts acquired rhônepoulenc jardin continental europes largest consumer lawn and garden products company rhônepoulenc jardin manufactures and sells a full line of consumer lawn and garden pesticides fertilizers and growing media products in france germany the benelux countries austria italy and spain   scotts acquired the shamrock brand of uk and irish peat products form bord na mona ireland   scotts entered into a collaboration with the monsanto company to apply biotechnology products to the turfgrass and ornamental plants business under the agreement scotts and monsanto agreed to share technologies including monsantos extensive genetic library of plant traits and scotts proprietary gene gun technology to produce transgenic turfgrasses and ornamental plants   scotts completed an acquisition with asef — a privately held beneluxbased lawn and garden products company asef is a leading consumer lawn and garden products company—with operations in the netherlands and belgium — selling fertilizers growing media and pesticides   entering into the pesticide industry scotts completed agreements with monsanto company for exclusive us canada uk france germany and australia agency and marketing rights to monsantos consumer roundup herbicide products and for the purchase of the ortho and related lawn and garden businesses   scotts acquired substral a leading consumer fertilizer brand in many european countries including germany austria belgium france and nordics scotts also purchased smith  hawken a leading brand of gardeninspired products that includes pottery watering equipment gardening tools outdoor furniture and live goods   scotts entered into the us wild bird food market through the acquisition of the morning song brand   scotts miraclegro sells wild bird food line to global harvest foods ltd   scotts miraclegro buys general hydroponics and vermicrop organics to move into the marijuana market under the name hawthorne gardening company   scotts lawn service merges with servicemasters trugreen becoming the largest lawn care company in north america   the hawthorne gardening also purchased gavita horticultural lighting and american agritech known as botanicare to fill out their cannabis portfolio   scotts acquired blossom a california manufacturer of internet enabled sprinkler systems brandsedit united statesedit black magic blossom bovung earthgro ecoscraps gavita general hydroponics greenlight hawthorne gardening company hyponex miraclegro ortho ortho elementals osmocote scotts scotts lawn service supersoil tomcat vermicrop organics whitney farms outside the usedit celaflor evergreen fertiligene gavita holland bv kb pathclear scotts ecosense substral weedol referencesedit  a b nyse smg  financial statements googlecom   the scotts miraclegro company the scotts miraclegro company retrieved    scottscom about us the scotts miraclegro company retrieved    scottscom about us the scotts miraclegro company archived from the original on october   retrieved    httpwwwseattletimescomnationworldmiraclegrogoespublicinbackingromney  huntspencer scotts to pay  million in fines the columbus dispatch columbus oh  january   united states environmental protection agency scotts miraclegro will pay  million in criminal fines and civil penalties for violations of federal pesticide laws press release  september   watrud ls lee eh fairbrother a burdick c reichman jr bollman m storm m king g van de water pk october  evi