lizer technologies such as osmocote along with other brands including metromix banrot and peters in addition sierra also brought on board a wellestablished international organization for manufacturing sales and distribution this organization began in  when archer daniels midland company produced the firstever resincoated controlledrelease fertilizer   scotts merged with miraclegro products inc   miracle care garden ltd approximately a third of the growing uk lawn and garden products company was owned by miraclegro at the time of the  merger and in january  scotts purchased the remaining interest in the company   scotts acquired emerald green lawn service which would become scotts lawn service in    scotts purchased privately held levington horticulture ltd to expand into the uk horticulture market   the company acquired the organics company earthgro inc expanding access to mass merchant retailers and home centers in the northeast region   the company acquired  ownership of plant breeding company sanford scientific inc ssi   scotts acquired rhônepoulenc jardin continental europes largest consumer lawn and garden products company rhônepoulenc jardin manufactures and sells a full line of consumer lawn and garden pesticides fertilizers and growing media products in france germany the benelux countries austria italy and spain   scotts acquired the shamrock brand of uk and irish peat products form bord na mona ireland   scotts entered into a collaboration with the monsanto company to apply biotechnology products to the turfgrass and ornamental plants business under the agreement scotts and monsanto agreed to share technologies including monsantos extensive genetic library of plant traits and scotts proprietary gene gun technology to produce transgenic turfgrasses and ornamental plants   scotts completed an acquisition with asef — a privately held beneluxbased lawn and garden products company asef is a leading consumer lawn and garden products company—with operations in the netherlands and belgium — selling fertilizers growing media and pesticides   entering into the pesticide industry scotts completed agreements with monsanto company for exclusive us canada uk france germany and australia agency and marketing rights to monsantos consumer roundup herbicide products and for the purchase of the ortho and related lawn and garden businesses   scotts acquired substral a leading consumer fertilizer brand in many european countries including germany austria belgium france and nordics scotts also purchased smith  hawken a leading brand of gardeninspired products that includes pottery watering equipment gardening tools outdoor furniture and live goods   scotts entered into the us wild bird food market through the acquisition of the morning song brand   scotts miraclegro sells wild bird food line to global harvest foods ltd   scotts miraclegro buys general hydroponics and vermicrop organics to move into the marijuana market under the name hawthorne gardening company   scotts lawn service merges with servicemasters trugreen becoming the largest lawn care company in north america   the hawthorne gardening also purchased gavita horticultural lighting and american agritech known as botanicare to fill out their cannabis portfolio   scotts acquired blossom a california manufacturer of internet enabled sprinkler systems brandsedit united statesedit black magic blossom bovung earthgro ecoscraps gavita general hydroponics greenlight hawthorne gardening company hyponex miraclegro ortho ortho elementals osmocote scotts scotts lawn service supersoil tomcat vermicrop organics whitney farms outside the usedit celaflor evergreen fertiligene gavita holland bv kb pathclear scotts ecosense substral weedol referencesedit  a b nyse smg  financial statements googlecom   the scotts miraclegro company the scotts miraclegro company retrieved    scottscom about us the scotts miraclegro company retrieved    scottscom about us the scotts miraclegro company archived from